\par \pard\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 Am oberen und li. Rand: lat. Notizen des Schreibers \u252 \'fcber {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[0].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Sultan Saladin}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (\u8224 \'86 1193) und die Eroberung Konstantinopels:\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  Primus Soldanus dicebatur Zaricon \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 sonst: Saracon\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 secundus\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 filius eius Saldani \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 sonst: Saladin\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 qui circa annum mcxc \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 [\u252 \'fcberschrieben: \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 1190\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ] \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 cum Thurcis totam fere terram promissionis abstulit a Christianos ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  - \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... tenet in homagio sub imperatore de Cathay Grant Gcan \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 sonst: Grand Can\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 . 
