\pard\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (58\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 -61\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 Exzerptsammlung Teil II\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 : {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[0].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Ps.-Al-Kindi}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[1].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Al-Farghani}}\plain \f1\b\scaps\lang1033\fs24 ,\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24  {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[2].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Ptolomaeus}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[3].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Orosius}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[4].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Sallustius}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[5].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Petrus de Alliaco}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[6].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 John Mandeville}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[7].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Vincentius Bellovacensis}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[8].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Alfonsus de Spina}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 .
\par \pard\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Et hoc de mirabilibus mundi. Ex libraria 29. \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 [evtl. Verweis auf die Hs. G 29\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 2\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , vgl. MBK II, S. 373\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 15-38\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ] (a) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Alexander devictis gentibus in partibus orientis, gentes aspectu terribiles ... \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (58\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... terram quasi aream proposuit expurgare. Item ibidem eciam habetur de purgatorio Patricii\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (b) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 In libro differentiarum 30 Alfragani septimum clima incipit ab oriente et septentrione regionum Gog et Magog ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (59\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (c) >\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 S\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 <\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 cithia iuxta Rha flu\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 vium\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  usque flexionem cuius situs\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... Hic Ptolomeus in libro quinto capitulo nono de Scythia intra Imaun montem et de Scythia extra eundem montem Ptholomeus libro sexto capitulo xii\u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (d) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 De regionibus Egipto adiacentibus secundum Orosium: Post Egyptum superiorem Orosius a parte meridiana ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (59\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 \u8230 \'85 Tracia secundum Orosium post Messina locatur \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (60\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 )\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (e) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item secundum Salustium qui Egesippo hystoriographo teste \u8230 \'85 - \u8230 \'85 Getulia autem Africe pars mediterranea est qui a Gethis seu Gothis nomen accepit secundum Salustium\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (f) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Caspium autem mare duplex esse legimus ... - \u8230 \'85 Circa vero hoc mare inter montes Caspios gentes Gog et Magog incluse sunt dicit Pe\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 trus\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  Ca\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 meracensis?, s. u.\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 \u8230 \'85 Item  Pe\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 trus\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  Ca\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 meracensis? = Petrus de Alliaco episcopus Cameracensis ?\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  in libro de legibus et sectis contra supersticiosos astronomos \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (g) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item Ethicus philosophus dicit in sua cosmographia \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (60\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 )\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  quod gens qui fuit clausa inter portas Caspias \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (h) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item in itinerario magistri Johannes Mandeueldi capitulo xli scribit quomodo a prouincia Cathay in orientem sunt terras imperii Tartarorum \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (i) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Tradit scolastica historia \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (j) [Einf\u252 \'fcgung dess Kompilators:] \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Ego legi historiam Alexandri Magni ex toto et non reperi quod aliquid dixisset aut mencionem fecisset de montibus et de portibus Caspias nisi tamen in uno loco et unico capitulo ubi sic stat: Alexander \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (61\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 )\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  intrauit Pori ciuitatem \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (k) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item libro quinque Speculi historialis \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (l) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item in libro qui intitulatur Fortilicium \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (!) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 fidei tertio libro \u8230 \'85 - \u8230 \'85Hoc ibi scilicet in Fortilicio.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Exzerpte u. a. aus (a) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Ps.-Al-Kindi:\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[0].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Epistola \u8218 \'82Prudenti viro\rquote }}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , Edition: C. S. F. \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Burnett\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , An Apocryphal Letter from the Arabic Philosopher Al-Kindi to Theodore, Frederick II\rquote s Astrologer, Concerning Gog et Magog, the Enclosed Nations, and the Scourge of the Mongols, in: Viator, Medieval and Renaissance Studies, 15 (1984), S. 151-167, zur \u220 \'dcberlieferung  ebd., S. 159-163; zum \u8218 \'82Purgatorium sancti Patricii\rquote  vgl. N. F. \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Palmer\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , in: \plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 2\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 VL 2 (1980), Sp. 715-717; (b) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Al-Farghani\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (Alfraganus), {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[1].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Liber triginta differentiarum}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , wohl in der \u220 \'dcbersetzung des {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[9].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Johannes Ispalensis}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , das Werk mehrfach im Katalog der Erfurter Universit\u228 \'e4t, jedoch nicht im Bibliothekskatalog der Kartause genannt, vgl. MBK II, S. 22\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 41f.\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , 24\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 40f.\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , 25\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 36f\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , 28\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 4\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , 36\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 24\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (c) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Ptolomaeus\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[2].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Liber Geographiae}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , lib. V, cap. 9; lib. VI, cap. 12; (d) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Orosius\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[3].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Historiarum adversum paganos libri VII}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , vgl. CSEL 5; (e) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Sallustius\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[4].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Historiae}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ?; (f) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Petrus de Alliaco\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[5].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 De legibus et sectis contra supersticiosos astronomos}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , zum Werk s. u. 124\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (g) Ethicus philosophus, {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[6].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Cosmographia}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , nicht identifiziert; (h) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 John Mandeville\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[7].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Itinerarium}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , cap. 40, Edition und Literatur s. o. 57\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (j) {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[8].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Historia Alexandri Magni}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (k) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Vincentius Bellovacensis\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[9].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Speculum historiale}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (l) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Alfonsus de Spina\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[10].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Fortalitium fidei}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , s. o. 57\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 .}

