\pard\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (69\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 -76\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 Exzerptsammlung Teil V: Material {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[0].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 \u252 \'fcber die Tartaren, T\u252 \'fcrken, Armenier, Sarazenen}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 : {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[0].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 John Mandeville}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[1].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Hugo de Novo Castro}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[2].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Jacobus Philippus Foresti}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[3].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Isidorus Hispalensis}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[4].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Vincentius Bellovacensis}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[5].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Jacobus de Vitriaco}}\plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24  etc.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (69\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r-v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (a) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Nunc breviter intendo cursim describere aliquas magnarum regionum et insularum imperie Tartarie. Primo illas que descendunt a prouincia Cathay per septentrionalem plagam ... - ... potestatis magni imperatoris Indie, qui semper vocatur presbyter Johannes. \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Zeile gestrichen\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (69\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (b) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Kommentar des Kompilators:\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Zeile gestrichen: \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Et sic videtur michi ...\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Sed utrum hoc sit verum quod per gentes Gog et Magog debent intelligi gens Taratarorum ignoro ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (70\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (c) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Super verba ista scilicet sancti Methodii ut supra ante quatuor folia circa signum X \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (s. o. 63\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 scribit doctor Hugo Parisiensis de Nouo Castro in Libello de uictoria Christi contra Antichristum ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (d) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item in complemento cronicarum ita habetur ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (70\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (e) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 chronikal. Nachrichten:\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  Item ibidem circa annum domini 905 Ungari qui et Hunni gens Scythica ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (f) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item Isidorus ethymologiarum: Ungnos \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 sonst: Hugnos\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 antea Hunnos uocatos, postremo a rege suo Auares appellatos ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 marginaler Verweis auf Schaltzettel Bl. 71: \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 cedula nota\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , s. u.\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (70\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , 72\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (g) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 chronikalische Aufzeichnungen zur t\u252 \'fcrkischen Geschichte und zur Erorberung Konstantinopels\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item anno 1260 Latini perdiderunt regnum Constantinopolitanum et ad Grecos pervenit ... Exinde Paleologorum imperii principium exortum est Michael Paleologus Grecos \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (72\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r-v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (h) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Mahumetus seu Mehemeth Sulthan id est Soldan magnus Turcorum et Grecorum imperator \u8230 \'85 anno domini 1481 nonas Mayas anno etatis sue quadragesimo octauo uitam finiuit et Constantinopolim se sepeliri fecit \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 De Sumcassiona \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (!) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 magno rege nota. Sumcassianus felicissimus Persarum et Armenie rex et victoriarum pater cui proprium nomen fuit Assimbeus. Isto anno scilicet domini 1433 Zensa \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 sonst: Zenza\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  regem Persarum interfecit et Persis imperare cepit \u8230 \'85 - \u8230 \'85 Mahumeth Assimbei Sumcassiani filius anno domini 1477 patre defunto in regnis Parthorum, Persarum, Medorum, Mesopotanie et Armenie regnare cepit et nunc usque 8 annis regnat\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 s. o. Geschichte\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 .\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (72\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 -74\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (i) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 chronikalische Aufzeichnungen zum Mongolenherrscher Timur Lenk\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Item hic superius tactum est de magno Tamburlano. Qui uixit circa annum domini 1402 \u8230 \'85 - \u8230 \'85 Sicut legitur de istis Tartaris. Lege nunc istam cedulam scilicet primum latus ceduli \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (s. u. Schaltzettel 73\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 )\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  de principio regni Tartararum.\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (74\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r-v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (j) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Kommentar des Kompilators:\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Michi videtur ex scripturis quod Tartarorum gens est de gente Gog et Magog. \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 marginaler Vermerk: \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 In libro Speculi historialis libro 30 hoc habetur:\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Anno domini 1202 secundum quosdam thartari post occisionem domini sui ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (74\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (k) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 De successoribus Machometi \u8230 \'85 prophete Sarracorum. Aconensis \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 = \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Jacobus de Vitriaco\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 in libro de rebus et statu terrae orientalium narrat quod post mortem Machometi Saraceni quendam ex discipulis Machometi loco eius eligerunt ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (76\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (l) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Erorberungen der t\u252 \'fcrkischen Armee:\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Sed interim multa mala in ecclesia dei operati sunt Turci scilicet in captione ciuitatum Nigroponti \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 venezianische Hauptfestung Negroponte, 1470 durch Mehmed II. erst\u252 \'fcrmt\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  et Ydrumi \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (?)\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  Nicosia ... Et eciam circa Ungariam anno 1483 non modicam confusionem et stragem perpessi sunt\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (76\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (m) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 De quodam magno domino. Meles Bleusem Betice seu Granate rex genere Maurus religioneque Mahumetheus ... - ... Hunc itaque Bleusem regem Ferdinandus anterioris Hispanie et Lusitanie ac Arragonie \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (!) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 et Cicilie rex una cum Elizabeth uxore christianissima \u8230 \'85 cum maximo eorum tryumpho eidem abstulerunt, quarum uota ipse dominus Ihesus ad finem usque feliciter perducere dignetur.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (a) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 John Mandeville\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[1].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Itinerarium}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , cap. 40, Edition und Literatur s. o. 57\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (c) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Hugo Parisiensis de Novo Castro\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[2].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 De victoria Christi contra Antichristum}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , auch in der Hs. H 74 der Erfurter Kartause, vgl. MBK II, S. 408\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 24-26\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (d) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Jacobus Philippus Foresti\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[3].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Supplementum chronicarum}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (?), s. o. 54\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (f) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Isidoris Hispalensis\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[4].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Etymologiae}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  IX,2,66; (g) historischer Abri\u223 \'df der {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[5].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Geschichte Konstantinopels}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , erw\u228 \'e4hnt werden die byzantinischen Herrscher seit \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Michael VIII. {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[6].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Palaiologos}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (1224-1282), der Mongolenherrscher {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[7].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Timur Lenk}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (\u8218 \'82Tamerlanus\rquote , reg. 1370-1404) sowie die Eroberung Konstantinopels durch {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[8].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Sultan Mehmed II.}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (1432-1481) im Jahre 1453; (h) Textbeginn beider Abschnitte \u252 \'fcbereinstimmemd mit: \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Hartmann Schedel\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , Liber chronicarum, N\u252 \'fcrnberg: Anton Koberger, 12.VII.1493, f. CCLVI\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , CCLIX\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , vgl. GW M40784, eingesehenes Digitalisat: Weimar, HAAB, Inc 118 (\plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Raffel\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  Nr. 440): http://ora-web.swkk.de/digimo_online/digimo.entry?source=digimo.Digitalisat_anzeigen&a_id=4580 \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Stand 12.11.09\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ); (j) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Vincentius Bellovacensis\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[6].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Speculum historiale}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , pars IV, lib. 30, s. o. 64\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (k) \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24 Jacobus de Vitriaco\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[7].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 De rebus et statu terrae orientalium (= Historia orientalis}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ?); (m) Notizen zur {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[8].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Eroberung der Iberischen Halbinsel}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  durch {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[9].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 K\u246 \'f6nig Ferdinand III. von Kastilien und Leon}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  (\u8224 \'86 1252) im Jahr 1236.}

