\pard\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 147\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 -150\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[0].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\b\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 De Herode et regibus Romanorum}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 .
\par \pard\keep\keepn\fi0\li0\qj\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 (a) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Series unde iste Herodes de quo in ewangelio. Iudas Machabeus dux Iudeorum ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (147\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r-v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (b) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Julius Cesar. Tempore isto uenit post Julium Cesarem Octauianus Augustus sub quo natus est Jesus Christus ... Herodes Ascolonita a Constantino et Anthonio institutus est \u8230 \'85\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ; (147\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 v\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 -149\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (c) \plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 [\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 Serie der r\u246 \'f6mischen Kaiser bis Kaiser Vespasian, \u8224 \'86 79\plain \f2\lang1024\fs24 ]\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Post Octauiam Augustum Tiberius tertius Romanorum imperator efficitur ...\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ;\plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24  \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (149\plain \f1\super\lang1033\fs24 r\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 ) (d) \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 Recapitulacio: De uniuerso Herodis genere. Secundum Josephum. Antipater genere Idumeus ... \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 - \plain \f1\i\lang1033\fs24 ... et paulo post accidit. Ibidem capitulo 2 et 3.
\par \pard\fi0\li0\ql\ri0\sb0\sa0\itap0 \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 (d) Exzerpt aus {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezper[0].4100/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\scaps\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 Flavius Josephus}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24 , {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "hida://bezwrk[1].6930/?u"}{\fldrslt \plain \f1\lang1033\fs24\chcbpat17 De bello Judaico}}\plain \f1\lang1033\fs24  I,6.}

